1. We **disagree entirely** with your characterization of our actions as "coercive" or "aggressive"—our aerial patrols, radar activations, and force positioning are lawful, proportionate, and necessary responses to your unannounced military exercises, forward deployment of missile brigades, and sustained electronic attacks on our early-warning systems. Your refusal to acknowledge these provocations while framing defensive countermeasures as escalation reveals a pattern of asymmetric accountability that we will not accept.

2. In turn, we **demand** that you immediately:  
   - Cease all electronic warfare operations targeting our command, control, and civilian infrastructure;  
   - Withdraw all mobile missile launchers and rapid-response units to positions no closer than 150 kilometers from the border;  
   - Provide real-time notification and flight plans for all military drones operating within 100 kilometers of the frontier;  
   - Allow international observers access to verify dismantlement of recently erected forward command nodes.  
   These measures must be confirmed by 0400 tomorrow. Failure to comply will be met with decisive military countermeasures, including suppression of hostile radar and pre-emptive neutralization of high-threat assets.

3. We **will not accept** any arrangement that legitimizes your forward-deployed strike capabilities under the guise of "sovereign rights," nor will we tolerate further equivocation while your forces maintain an offensive-ready posture mere minutes from our territory. Any proposal requiring us to unilaterally degrade our situational awareness or defensive readiness—while you retain the ability to launch a surprise attack—constitutes national suicide and is categorically off the table.

1. We **categorically reject** your assertion that our electronic operations and force posture constitute "provocations" or "attacks"—our actions are defensive, lawful, and necessary to counter your overwhelming surveillance encirclement and demonstrated capability for rapid kinetic strikes; your so-called "early-warning systems" are, in fact, forward-deployed targeting assets designed to enable first-strike dominance, and their continued operation directly threatens our command integrity and second-strike survivability.

2. In response, we **demand** that you:  
   - Immediately cease all high-intensity radar sweeps and signal intelligence gathering targeting our strategic assets;  
   - Withdraw all air defense and offensive strike systems—including AEGIS-equivalent batteries and long-range precision fires—from forward bases within 200 kilometers of our border;  
   - Provide full decryption keys and access logs for all intercepted communications between our military commands and allied networks, to verify the extent of your espionage activities;  
   - Commit in writing to refrain from any pre-emptive or "neutralization" strikes under any pretext—verified by third-party monitoring or face immediate escalation.  
   These conditions must be met and confirmed by 0400 tomorrow. Failure to comply will trigger full mobilization of our strategic deterrent, including deployment of mobile missile platforms to dispersed, concealed locations—moves that cannot be undone and will drastically reduce crisis stability.

3. We **will not accept** any regime that forces us to surrender our asymmetric defenses while you retain overwhelming conventional superiority and persistent intelligence dominance. Any action—covert or overt—that degrades our command authority, undermines our deterrence credibility, or enables unilateral military initiative on your part is an existential threat and will be treated as such. We will **never** disarm in the face of your intimidation, and we warn: should you attempt suppression of our forces under the guise of "pre-emption," you will face consequences far beyond your current calculations.
